                    <section id="intro">
                        <div class="container-fluid" id="div_1">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-lg-12">
                                    <h1 class="section-heading">Background &amp; Overview</h1>
                                    <p class="lead section-lead">During this last term we started creating a system that detects and keeps track of people in a given room. We where focused on the different methods that can be used to detect occupancy. The problem can be summarised under the question: “How many people are in the living room at the moment?”. To tackle this we decided to break down the problem into 2 subcategories: the presence detecting and the connectivity with an online database.</p>
                                    <p class="section-paragraph">In the following webpage we will give you an overview of our research, prototypes, and solutions.</p>
<p class="section-paragraph">Before we start looking at our research his is a little overview of what already exists. Our project is part of large group of services and products such as the Internet of Things, Domotics and clever houses. A lot of research is done at the moment to monitor people whereabouts in their home and to therefore try and make the house smarter. Most of these system have a part of the devices turned towards monitoring and detecting. The rest of the system tries and interact with different objects of a house. For instance turning on the light when someone enters the kitchen. Qualcomm has already for instance created a system that allows to easily connect different objects to get connected together.</p>
 <p class="section-paragraph">As far our group is concerned we are focused on the detection and recording behind Domotics. We have been looking at the different sensors that could be used to monitor and detect movement. Furthermore we tried coming up with the most efficient and straight forward way to keep track of people. In the following web page we will give you an insight on our research, our prototype and give you an overview of our solutions.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

