                        <div class="container-fluid" id="div_3">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-lg-12">
                                    <h1 class="section-heading">Project Requirements and Scope</h1>
                                    <p class="lead section-lead">The scope of our projects is you have understood very wide. It goes from the point where the system just signals if a room is occupied to the exact number of people and their location in the room. Ideally the requirements would be:
<br>
<ul>
<li>A single nice and discrete device than can be plugged somewhere in the room.</li>
<li>This device would constantly informed a database with the state of the room.</li>
<li>It would send constantly send monitoring information and signal detected.</li>
<li>It would allow an instant and precise update of the occupancy of the room.</li>
</ul>
<br>
However in this situation a problem quickly arise: there is no sensor or system precise and efficient enough to cover an entire room. This firstly impacts the number of  devices that would have to be used. We have decided to divid these devices into 2 categories .The first are sensors that cover the doors to monitor the in and out signals of people either entering or leaving the room. Finally the second type of sensor would do a global monitoring of the room to confirm what the doors are saying. Therefore here are the requirements we have setup for this project:
<br>
Creating a device that covers doors.
Simple devices that can be hidden at strategic points in the room.
Each of these device have to be connected to the network in some way.
<br>
Regarding the connectivity we have to send the data collected by our sensors to a database defined by the other group. Here the requirements we have set for it:
<br>
The package of information sent has to include: A timestamp, the ID of the sensor, and what it has detected.
If the Sensor is not on the door it might not send signals but constant update on its readings.
<br>
To summarise we decided in the first term of the project to do research on presence detecting; testing and dressing up a table of all the different sensors that can be used; finally having a first prototype system that detects something and sends the information to a storage place.
<br>
To visualise a bit where we are situated in the presence detecting stage have a close look at the following figure. The more we go towards the right end of the arrow the more the solution complicates itself and the more problems arrise.</p>
                                   
                                </div>
