                        <div class="container-fluid" id="div_8">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-lg-12">
                                    <h1 class="section-heading">Testing</h1>
                                    <p class="lead section-lead">To test each sensor we tried to find the best environment in which to test our softwares. At the moment these are simple rooms with one door. For the moment we just want to prove that our solution works. It only is a proof a concept. The aim of the testing was to see in which environment was each sensor the most appropriate and what conditions could affect their state. We realised that most of the sensors where easily affected by their surroundings. Meaning that depending on where they were located the results would vary.
<br>
Humidity
<br>
<ul>
<li>Quick change in temperatures (entrance)</li>
<li>A lot of noise (people passing by)</li>
<li>Colors of the environment and material used around.</li>
</ul>
<br>
These results have a direct impact on the possible location of our devices. For instance a human heat temperature sensor cannot be positions at the entrance of a house. The quick changes in temperature that might hide the humans signature.
<br>
Sensors and Connectivity devices:
<br>
The prototype we have:
In the following table are all the sensors we have studied, and tested and on top of it all the different possibilities to connect our system to the network.</p>
                                   
